Talks between the employer and Nehawu have reached a deadlock since discussions started at the beginning of the year. CAPE TOWN - The National Education, Health and Allied Workers' Union (Nehawu) has vowed to shut down operations at the National Financial Aid Scheme (NSFAS)'s head offices in Wynberg in Cape Town over performance bonuses.Talks between the employer and Nehawu, which represents 80% of NSFAS workers, have reached a deadlock since discussions started at the beginning of the year.The trade union says NSFAS has refused to take seriously their concerns over what it calls the flawed performance assessment process.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)